column1:
*sigh* Man, reality's only a couple hours away
now...

Oh, give it up already. There'll be plenty of fun
in your future too.
Time to crack open those books.
Sounds like I gotta brace myself then!

Yes, we must all return to our own paths
and stay focused on our goals.

Oh! And if we never go to sleep, then the
night truly never ends!

No. Playtime has to end at some point.
Our real-world responsibilities need
to take priority.
Makoto, do you need a route to Tokyo?
Yes, Sophia, thank you. Could you do the honors?
A Jail... I suddenly smell a Jail!

Hang on now! I thought we shut down that
EMMA bullshit!
Shouldn't all the Jails be gone!?

Can you tell how long the Jail smell's been
here?

It wasn't here when we first arrived, but now...
I have no doubt.

And it's still spreading! What is this? It's already
wider than—

Where are you right now!? Are you watching
the news!?

Now, for breaking news on the virtual assistant
EMMA:

Despite recent claims of being shut down, it
appears an unidentified system malfunction
is preventing proper deactivation.

EMMA development company Madicce has
requested the public avoid accessing EMMA
in any way at this time...
I don't know why this is happening, but...

I do know that EMMA's servers are located in
the Tokyo Radio Tower.

I also know for a fact that it was successfully
turned off and the app became inaccessible...

But now? It's all back up and running. Konoe
doesn't know why—neither does anyone still
at Madicce.

Someone intentionally rebooted the server?
Nah, Madicce would've already been there to
stop them...

Wait, then that would mean some genuine sci-fi
stuff is happening here!
Hey—say somethin' if you're on, EMMA!
Hello, how can I help you?

Is it accessing different ports or something?
But, how...?
It had to have been a mistake.

Zenkichi, we've got another problem—Sophia
just smelled a Jail.
What!? Are you sure that's what it is!?

I have no doubt. It's an enormous Jail, spanning
the Tokyo area all the way to Yokohama.
The epicenter is the Tokyo Radio Tower.
Looks like we've got a new destination.
I'm already headed your way! Be there soon!
